# Fluid Brand Intelligence Skills

This project includes the full Fluid Brand Intelligence pipeline for generating and validating branded content. The skills are defined as Claude Code commands in `.claude/commands/` but the underlying agent logic applies to any AI tool working in this project.

## Available Pipelines

### Generate (create new branded content)
Each pipeline chains 4 agents: copy -> layout -> styling -> spec-check.

| Pipeline | Use When | Output |
|----------|----------|--------|
| **fluid-generate-web** | Creating new web pages or sections | Responsive HTML/CSS |
| **fluid-generate-social** | Creating Instagram (1080x1080) or LinkedIn (1200x627) posts | Fixed-dimension HTML |
| **fluid-generate-onepager** | Creating letter-size (8.5x11in) one-pagers | Print-ready HTML |
| **fluid-generate-slides** | Creating 16:9 slide decks | Multi-slide HTML |

### Transform (modify existing content)
| Pipeline | Use When | Agents |
|----------|----------|--------|
| **fluid-brand** | Reskin existing HTML with Fluid visuals (preserve layout) | styling -> spec-check |
| **fluid-redesign** | Redesign layout AND apply brand | layout -> styling -> spec-check |
| **fluid-rewrite** | Rewrite copy to match Fluid voice (no visual changes) | copy -> spec-check (voice mode) |

## Agent Definitions

Full agent specs are in `.claude/agents/`. When generating or validating content, follow these roles:

### Copy Agent (`.claude/agents/copy-agent.md`)
- Reads `brand/voice-guide/` for voice rules
- Reads `brand/voice-guide/products/*.md` for product-specific messaging
- Writes pain-first, scenario-specific copy
- Never uses banned words (see `brand/hard-rules.md`)
- FLFont tagline follows `[benefit]. [contrast].` pattern

### Layout Agent (`.claude/agents/layout-agent.md`)
- Selects from archetypes in `archetypes/social/`
- Matches content shape to best archetype
- Fills structural HTML slots

### Styling Agent (`.claude/agents/styling-agent.md`)
- Reads `brand/patterns/*.md` for all visual rules
- Uses assets from `assets/` (fonts, brushstrokes, circles, logos)
- Applies: colors, fonts, brushstrokes, circle emphasis, footer
- All asset paths must be RELATIVE (e.g., `assets/fonts/flfontbold.ttf`)

### Spec-Check Agent (`.claude/agents/spec-check-agent.md`)
- Validates against `brand/hard-rules.md`
- Checks: font usage, accent color consistency, brushstroke rules, footer structure, visual hierarchy, copy tone
- Produces JSON report with blocking issues (severity >= 81) and warnings
- Fix loop: up to 3 iterations for blocking issues

## Key Rules for Any Agent

1. **Read `BRAND.md` first** — it has the complete brand summary
2. **One accent color per design** — pick from: `#FF8B58` (orange), `#42b1ff` (blue), `#44b574` (green), `#c985e5` (purple)
3. **Font system is closed** — NeueHaas (headlines, weight 900), Inter (body, weight 300-400), flfontbold (taglines only). No other fonts. Only `sans-serif` as fallback.
4. **Brushstrokes use `mix-blend-mode: screen`** — opacity 0.10-0.25, edges bleed off canvas
5. **No new colors** — palette is fixed (see BRAND.md)
6. **Asset paths are relative** — never `/assets/`, always `assets/`
7. **Problem before solution** — in copy, name the pain first
